"Statistically significant" is one of those phrases scientists would love to take back and rename.

"Significant" suggests importance; but the test of statistical significance, developed by the British statistician R.A. Fisher, doesn't measure the importance or size of an effect; only whether we are able to distinguish it, using our keenest statistical tools, from zero. 

"Statistically noticeable" or "Statistically discernable" would be much better.

